title.rendered: Britney Spears Music Video Tease: A Mind-Blowing, Life-Altering Five Seconds

content.rendered:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

It’s a whole five seconds, at least 1-2 of which aren’t actually footage from the video, but we’ll take what we can get. Right, Britney Spears fans?

Below, we have your first video look at Spears’ new music video for “Hold It Against Me,” the hit single from her upcoming album, Femme Fatale.

Wearing a flowly white gown, Brit is seen in a room full by TVs, showing her from multiple views, like security cameras. That’s it. It’s real short.

Even more ridiculous? This is the first of 14 blink-and-you-miss-it teasers for the video, which will roll out each day until the full premiere.

It’s will be interesting to see if there is any dancing included in the subsequent clips, given the rumors if a dance double being used in the shoot.

What do you think? Excited for the video? Willing to hold out and wait for the final product? Psyched for a few seconds per day? Comment below.
